author: skywalkerfan52
title: Random minifigure history review: Darth Vader with light -up lightsaber
review: Today's minifigure review is Darth Vader with light-up lightsaber from international toy fair Nuremberg, Germany 2005 and was free. This was only available in 2005 for Revenge of the Sith for only a limited amount of time. Today its worth like the new Mos Eisley Cantina coming out this year. This is very rare because of Vader's light-up lightsaber. When you push his head down, the lightsaber lights up. The head, torso, and legs all stay together to make it work. The only thing that is removable is his helmet and the light part of the lightsaber. He has his grey burnt head and comes with a black cape. There is a panel on the back of the torso just in case you need to change the batteries once they die. He comes with a 2-4 black brick. I hope you enjoy this little history of Darth Vader with light-up lightsaber.
